Arduino: Any Arduino board will work for this project.
7-Segment Display: A common cathode or common anode 7-segment display (4 digits preferred).
Resistors: Typically 220Ω or 330Ω resistors to limit the current to the LEDs in the 7-segment display.
Push Buttons: Two or more push buttons to set the hours and minutes.
Breadboard and Jumper Wires: For making the connections between components.
Real-Time Clock (RTC) Module
